-- Murdoch calls Dow Jones meeting 'constructive'
-- 
-- Mon Jun 4, 2007 5:56pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/06/04/us-dowjones-newscorp-murdoch-idUSWEN856520070604

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - News Corp. NWSa.N Chief Executive Rupert Murdoch said on Monday he had a constructive meeting with the Bancroft family that controls Dow Jones & Co. Inc. DJ.N about his $5 billion bid for the company. 

 Upon leaving the meeting, which lasted several hours in New York, Murdoch told reporters, "We had a very long and constructive meeting."